<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-11-30</DATELINE><TITLE>Cholesterol: fa(s)t-food for enterovirus genome replication</TITLE><BODY>Hijacking and remodeling of host membranes is an obligatory step in the replicative cycle of (+)RNA viruses, including enteroviruses. Ilnytska et al. unveiled in Cell Host & Microbe that enteroviruses usurp clathrin-mediated endocytosis to shuttle cholesterol to sites of genome replication and that cholesterol is needed for efficient replication.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>